<%# Phase 27 follow-up (2026-05-17) — Bundles outer shelf (formerly
    `_collections_shelf`). ONE horizontal-scroll row whose entries are
    tile-per-bundle (NOT one sub-shelf per bundle with game tiles
    inside). Clicking a tile opens a modal listing the games in that
    bundle (Turbo Frame fetches `/bundles/<id>/games_pane`); clicking
    a game in the modal navigates to the game's show page.

    Empty-state policy (2026-05-18 revision): the shelf chrome
    (heading + count chip + `[+]` create button + modal partial)
    renders UNCONDITIONALLY so the user can seed the first bundle
    from `/games` even when none exist yet. Only the tiles row is
    suppressed when the input list is empty — an empty row reads as
    "no bundles yet" without needing explicit empty-state copy.
    Bundles with zero games still never reach here (the controller
    narrows the scope to bundles with members) — they would just
    render as an empty composite, which the no-cover fallback covers.

    Wave F (2026-05-17) — shelf chrome flows through
    `Games::ShelfComponent`; per-bundle tile renders through
    `Games::BundleTileComponent`. The dialog frame partial
    (`bundles_modal`) is rendered as a sibling so the modal
    container exists in the DOM when the user clicks a tile OR clicks
    `[+]` (the create flow's Turbo Stream `replace`s this same node).

    Locals:
      bundles  ActiveRecord::Relation of Bundle rows, pre-filtered to
               those that own >= 1 member and pre-ordered alphabetical
               case-insensitive. Bundle composite covers are async-built
               (`BundleCoverBuild`); the tile component falls back to the
               shared placeholder SVG until the job stamps a checksum.
%>
<%
  bundles = local_assigns.fetch(:bundles)
%>
<%= render(Games::ShelfComponent.new(
      heading: t("games.bundles_shelf.heading"),
      count: bundles.size,
      heading_level: :h2,
      extra_classes: "shelf--bundles outer-shelf",
      shelf_kind: "outer-bundles",
      row_classes: "bundles-shelf-row",
      row_gap: "12px",
      row_align: "flex-start"
    )) do |shelf| %>
  <%# 2026-05-18 — `[+]` create button on the heading row, sibling to
      the count chip. Wraps a `button_to` so CSRF rides via the form;
      Turbo upgrades the submission to a Turbo Stream response
      (rendered by `bundles/create.turbo_stream.erb`). The form is
      sized to inline-flex so the bracketed button sits flush with
      the count chip without a block-level break. %>
  <% shelf.with_heading_extras do %>
    <%= button_to bundles_path, method: :post,
                  form: { style: "display: inline-flex; margin: 0;" },
                  class: "bracketed",
                  aria: { label: t("games.bundles_shelf.create_aria") } do %>[<span class="bl"><%= t("common.actions.add_short") %></span>]<% end %>
  <% end %>
  <% bundles.each do |bundle| %>
    <%= render(Games::BundleTileComponent.new(bundle: bundle)) %>
  <% end %>
<% end %>

<%# 2026-05-18 — Per-bundle delete-confirm dialogs. Rendered OUTSIDE
    the shelf component (and outside each bundle's `<a>` tile) so
    `<dialog>` is not nested inside interactive content. Each
    confirm modal carries the `bundle_delete_confirm` modal-actions
    key so the leader popup exposes `l dark mode` + `d delete` while
    it's open. %>
<% bundles.each do |bundle| %>
  <%= render ConfirmModalComponent.new(
        id: "confirm_delete_bundle_#{bundle.id}",
        title: t("bundles.delete_confirm_title", bundle: bundle.name),
        body: t("common.delete_irreversible"),
        confirm_label: t("common.actions.delete"),
        cancel_label: t("common.actions.cancel"),
        confirm_path: bundle_path(bundle),
        confirm_method: :delete,
        destructive: true,
        turbo: true,
        modal_actions_key: "bundle_delete_confirm") %>
<% end %>

<%= render "games/bundles_modal" %>
